tournament.motion:
This House would permit the selling of experiences

The Dreamscape is an innovative new technology that allows the transfer of experiences from one person to another. For the purposes of this debate, experiences include both the visual and emotional aspects of the memory.

This House, as an individual, would adopt religious closeness as opposed to religious distance

Religious closeness is the belief that God is everywhere and in everything. It preaches that individuals should consider the divine implications of their daily actions (e.g. cooking, gardening, work, etc.) and act as if they are doing them for God and in the name of God. Religious distance is the belief that God is distant from the world. It preaches that individuals can only find God by religious practices (e.g. praying, meditating, giving offers, etc.) and should only be contacted for significant decisions (e.g. choosing who to marry, etc.)
This House believes that choice feminism has done more harm than good for the feminist movement
This House believes that globalisation has failed the global poor

This House, as American universities, would limit freedom of speech among their staff and students

During his presidency, Donald Trump and his administration repeatedly threatened to withhold or restrict federal funding from universities and colleges in the United States. These threats were often tied to claims that institutions were promoting “radical left” ideology, restricting conservative speech, or failing to align with government priorities (for example, compliance with immigration enforcement or handling of campus protests). Federal funding for universities in the U.S. is substantial and covers research grants, student financial aid, and institutional support.

THP the integrationist over the accommodationist constitution-building model in post-independent state

The integrationist constitution-building model focuses on creating a unified national identity by maintaining uniform policies (those without group-specific variations), promoting a common culture/language, etc. Conversely, the accommodationist model seeks to protect national diversity through public acceptance of different identities, power-sharing agreements, etc.

TH, as the countries of SAARC would create a Common Trading Scheme

A Common Trading Scheme, like the European Union’s, removes tariffs, quotas, and customs checks between member states while applying a unified external tariff to non-members. This creates a single market where goods, services, capital, and people move freely. For example, products made in one country can be sold anywhere in the bloc without extra costs.

This house believes that political apathy is a form of immorality

Political apathy is a lack of interest or engagement in the political process. This can manifest as voter apathy, where people don't vote, or a broader disinterest in political issues, discussions, and events.
